	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-153879" number="53027" version="2965">
			<HEADING>Chapter 40: Certification of Radon and Other Vapors Levels in Certain Basement and Cellar Apartments</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19879" name="T24C040"/>Chapter 40: Certification of Radon and Other Vapors Levels in Certain Basement and Cellar Apartments</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-153885" number="53028" version="2965">
								<HEADING>§ 40-01 Scope and applicability.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19881" name="T24C040_40-01"/>§ 40-01 Scope and applicability.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153884" number="53029" version="2965">
									<PARA>This chapter applies to the certification for permissible maximum radon and other vapor levels in basement or cellar apartment units as required by § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="28-507.4.5.2" destination-id="0-0-0-0">28-507.4.5.2</LINK> of the Administrative Code and sections U202.9 and U202.10 of <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="BC AppU" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Appendix U</LINK> of the New York City Building Code (<LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="T28C008" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Chapter 8 of Title 28</LINK> of the Administrative Code). <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-153883" number="53030" version="2965">
								<HEADING>§ 40-02 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19883" name="T24C040_40-02"/>§ 40-02 Definitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153882" number="53031" version="2965">
									<PARA>Terms used in this chapter have the same meanings as the terms defined in § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="28-507.1" destination-id="0-0-0-0">28-507.1</LINK> of the Administrative Code and in Appendix <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="BC U102" destination-id="0-0-0-0">BC U102</LINK> of <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="BC AppU" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Appendix U</LINK> of the New York City Building Code. In addition, the following definitions shall apply: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153880" number="53032" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Certification</CHARFORMAT>” means the certification described in sections U202.9 or U202.10 of <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="BC AppU" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Appendix U</LINK> of the New York City Building Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153878" number="53033" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Certified Industrial Hygienist</CHARFORMAT>” means an individual certified as such by the Board for Global EHS Credentialing. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153877" number="53034" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">“Department</CHARFORMAT>” means the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153876" number="53035" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Qualified Environmental Professional</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as such term is defined in 6 NYCRR 375-1.2(ak). <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153875" number="53036" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Qualified radon tester</CHARFORMAT>” means an individual or firm certified as such by the American Association of Radon Scientists and Technologists, the National Radon Safety Board, the State of New Jersey, or the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-153874" number="53037" version="2965">
								<HEADING>§ 40-03 Methods of indoor air testing.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19885" name="T24C040_40-03"/>§ 40-03 Methods of indoor air testing.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153873" number="53038" version="2965">
									<PARA>All indoor air samples must be tested and reported by a laboratory certified by the New York State Environmental Laboratory Approval Program to analyze air samples for radon and volatile organic compounds using the appropriate sampling method: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153872" number="53039" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Radon.</CHARFORMAT> Testing of indoor air for radon must be conducted by a qualified radon tester using a testing device approved by the National Radon Proficiency Program, the National Radon Safety Board, or an equivalent program that verifies device compliance with the latest publication of ANSI/AARST (Performance Specification for Instrumentation Systems Designed to Measure Radon Gas in Air). <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153871" number="53040" version="2965">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Volatile Organic Compounds.</CHARFORMAT> Testing of indoor air for the volatile organic compounds listed in 24 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C040_40-06" destination-id="0-0-0-19891">40-06</LINK> must be conducted by a Certified Industrial Hygienist or Qualified Environmental Professional using the process described in United States Environmental Protection Agency, Method TO-15A: Determination of Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs) in Air Collected in Specially Prepared Canisters and Analyzed by Gas Chromatography–Mass Spectrometry (GC-MS), Sept. 2019. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-153870" number="53041" version="2965">
								<HEADING>§ 40-04 Radon level certification.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19887" name="T24C040_40-04"/>§ 40-04 Radon level certification.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-153869" number="53042" version="2965">
									<PARA>The radon level in any eligible basement or cellar apartment or ancillary dwelling unit must be less than two picocuries per liter of air based upon laboratory results as certified by a qualified radon tester. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-114]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
